{"componentChunkName":"component---src-page-post-tsx","path":"/working-remote-fix-the-missing-watercooler","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Markus Tacker","tagLine":"Software Crafter","description":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at Nordic Semiconductor.‚Äã\n\t\tMentor. Speaker. ‚ÄãConference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê","gitHubUrl":"https://github.com/coderbyheart/coderbyheart.com.git","siteUrl":"https://coderbyheart.com","twitter":"@coderbyheart","defaultCard":"https://images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3Jk4P6nFPNzaz1gsguktk8/350b7e4ddb2c7d86416243d9902920e2/social-card-default-2020.png"}}},"pageContext":{"page":{"id":"55958571-9682-501a-8257-630191fc803e","name":"working-remote-fix-the-missing-watercooler","relativeDirectory":"post","relativePath":"post/working-remote-fix-the-missing-watercooler.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/16WmaUrmImwWpAaHAW72vy/b1f1e3c7e6609b4da91b61fa2d15c5fa/hero.jpg?w=1599&h=999","alt":"Pixar Headquarter"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"This post series is a summary of my talk about the challenge working in\ndistributed teams.\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Find the other parts here."}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"./working-in-distributed-teams-the-three-most-important-challenges/"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The watercooler is a symbol for a central place in an office building where\neveryone walks by multiple times per day and which enables informal, accidental\nmeetings."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"How important this place is can be seen in this picture: this is the atrium in\nthe Pixar Headquarter. Steve Jobs himself altered the initial concept of the\narchitect and placed facilities like the restrooms, cafeterias, meeting rooms\nnext to each other in a central location to ensure employees need to leave their\nseclusion and bump into each other once in while. For Jobs only this would\nenable great ideas to form, information to spread and problems to be solved\nquickly. It also facilitates building relationships with colleagues and a sense\nof belonging. This obviously is lacking if you have no physical office but it is\nvital for every creative team to have an insight into what is happening in the\nwhole organization."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#working-out-loud","ariaLabel":"working out loud permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Working out loud"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"working-out-loud","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The way to fix this is probably not new to you but I can‚Äôt stress it enough:\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Start working out loud"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". You need to provide your coworkers with a constant\nstream of information about:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"what you are working on"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"what your impediments are"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ul","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"With this information available everyone can start making the connections to\ntheir own projects and contribute to solutions for your problems. This can‚Äôt\nhappen if you are away from your coworkers and only share a finished result of\nyour work once every other week. Obviously there is the need for a tool for that\nand by all means do not use email!"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I am having great results by using a team chat like "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Slack"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://slack.com/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\nfor the asynchronous sharing of what‚Äôs happening. Even if you don‚Äôt know Slack,\nyou will be familiar with the concept of chat rooms: a tool like Slack enables\nyou to have as many rooms as you like. This is different to Skype for instance\nwhere you only have a contact list and ad-hoc group chats. In Slack (or IRC if\nyou like) a history of messages is kept and even if people join a room at a\nlater point, they can re-read everything that has happened regarding the topic.\nEveryone is able to start following a certain topic and can contribute to it."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"There are usual three kinds of rooms:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Long-lasting general topic like "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"#tech"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"#marketing"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" and "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"#hiring"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" - I‚Äôd\nsay they usually emerge around every role you have in your organisation; you\ncould say these are communities of practice ‚Ä¶ but are also used to\ncommunicate news from these groups to the whole company in a less technical\nway."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Project-specific topics like "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"#website-relaunch"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" or "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"#our-mobile-app"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" in\nwhich you exchange about the progress of the project, these usually have a\ndiverse mix of people from all disciplines."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Short-lived topics like "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"#launch-of-big-feature"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"#special-event"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" which\ndeal usually have a high volume of exchange only for a few days and then can\nbe discarded."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ol","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"This granularity helps to better control the amount of information they will\nneed to consume because following everything is impossible. You need to care\nabout this! Of course we as developers have channels where every commit from our\nrepositories is posted, but I don‚Äôt get notified about every message in such a\nchannel, I selectively read them a few times a day. Slack enables you to specify\nnotification settings per channel and even have different settings depending on\nthe device so you can have more notifications if you are on your desktop or only\na few important ones if you are traveling. Make sure that the tool you are using\nhas this type of granularity when it comes to notifications and educate all your\nusers about them."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#more-bandwidth-video-chat","ariaLabel":"more bandwidth video chat permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"More bandwidth: video chat"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"more-bandwidth-video-chat","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"So much for the asynchronous part of working out loud but you will also need\nsomething that has a lot more bandwidth than text: video chat."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Everything that develops into a discussion with more than a few messages should\nbe taken to video. I always enjoy using\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Google Hangouts"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://hangouts.google.com/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" but if you don‚Äôt want to use\nGoogle services (like we did at my last company) you should check out\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Goto Meeting"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://www.gotomeeting.de/online-meetings/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" which is free for\neven more than three people and worked for my team very good. Both services\noffer a screen sharing option which is a real important feature for\ncollaboration ‚Ä¶ and a universal one; yes there is software that enables\nreal-time collaboration directly in your apps but screen sharing is universal.\nIf you need to remotely fix things on coworkers computer,\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"TeamViewer"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.teamviewer.com/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" is great. All these tools work\ncross-platform which you need to keep in mind, too (and I am neither on Mac nor\non Windows)."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Video chat not only has more bandwith than text but it also enables nonverbal\ncommunication which is really important to fully understand each other. We often\nused it to hang out together with microphones muted and listening to music but\neveryone could just speak up to the room if they had a question. And sometimes\npeople just need to vent, yes this may sound stupid but there is for instance\nsomething called rubber duck debugging which is a real thing!"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#-also-for-check-ins","ariaLabel":" also for check ins permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"‚Ä¶ also for "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"check-ins"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"-also-for-check-ins","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Besides the ad-hoc meetings for increased bandwidth and the occasional team\nhangout during the day I use videochat for all recurring meetings like daily\nstand-ups. I call them "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"check-ins"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Yes I know that there are tools that can collect daily stand-up information\nasynchronously ("},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"iDoneThis"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://idonethis.com/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":",\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Umantis Daily Highlights"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://marketing.umantis.com/deutsch/daily/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":",\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"a Slack bot"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://www.sofetch.io/products/standup-bot-private/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":") but I‚Äôm\nconvinced that you should use every chance you have to actually see and hear\neach other."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"daily standup"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" is where everyone states what they are working on and\nwhat their impediements are. This takes just a minute per person and should\nbe done after 15 minutes. Impediments need to be resolved immediately so we\nhave reserved an additional 15 minutes after the daily for 1-on-1s to\nresolve any pending issues. Everyone in the team knows to keep this slot\nfree for ad-hoc meetings. After that you can spread out again. Because the\ndaily stand-ups deal with detailed technical topics we only did them within\npeople of the same profession like developers, marketing, business people."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Once a week we then had a "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"product meeting"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" which brought together a wider\nrange of people, usually the product owner and if needed other specialists.\nThis meeting took between one and two hours on every Monday and was used to\nplan the upcoming week and readjust the backlog."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"And finally there were our weekly lunches: Once a week on every Tuesday at\n1pm everyone would gather together for a lunch. This is a great meeting\nbecause of its informal nature and you have a perfect ice-breaker for free:\n‚Äúwhat are you having for lunch over there?‚Äù That‚Äôs always fun! During the\nweekly lunch we‚Äôd go through every department and provide a brief update of\nwhat has happened. Bringing everyone together again creates the opportunity\nfor cross-chatter and random connections."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ol","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/0HLAHOA00P7ey1TZjfDN8/3b23f9cbd8b51ef6b7d5957e3fae56d0/remote-lunch.jpg?w=576&h=360","alt":"Weekly Lunch"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"By the way: this is a large flatscreen where we connected to our remotees ‚Ä¶\nwhat‚Äôs especially nice is that this large screen gives them a real physical\npresence because it provide a life-size image and a loud sound. And yes, getting\nthe technology right is always a pain. You need good internet connections,\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"good webcams (go for HD!)"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://amzn.to/1m1dVVk","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" and\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"good headsets"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://amzn.to/1m1g1Ez","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" ‚Ä¶ don‚Äôt go cheap on those."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"But occasionally every technology will fail. Usually the internet connection of\none person or the chat or video service entirely ‚Ä¶ which brings me to my first\nprotip:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#protip-1-have-a-fallback-ready","ariaLabel":"protip 1 have a fallback ready permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Protip #1: Have a fallback ready"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"protip-1-have-a-fallback-ready","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"In our case we usually had problems with the internet connection of one of our\ncolleagues and some times goto meeting was down. So we made sure that everyone\nknew how to switch over to a telephone conference provider. The information was\navailable in the wiki and as soon as problems arised we quickly switched to the\nfallback without much waiting in order to continue quickly without to many\nfailed attempts. Obviously this requires you to a) find a fallback and b) test\nit once in a while. For video conferencing we used "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Talky"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://talky.io/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" as\nan alternative. And alternative for a not working internet connection is using a\ndifferent medium, which is phones. "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"MyTelco"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://www.mytelco.de/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" provides\nfree dial in conference rooms, and usually everyone has flatrates on their\nphones these days."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"So many tools, I know ‚Ä¶ That‚Äôs why, my second protip is:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#protip-2-define-a-communication-escalation-process","ariaLabel":"protip 2 define a communication escalation process permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Protip #2: Define a communication escalation process!"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"protip-2-define-a-communication-escalation-process","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"What this means is that you establish a common understanding in your team, which\ncommunication tool is used for what. At my last workplace we had these rules:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Slack is the main communication medium used to push information and to clarify\nquestions, it is agreed upon that everyone is free to read messages in Slack\nwhenever it suits them. It is asynchronous and everyone must be okay with the\nfact that there may be hours between your question and a response."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The authorative tool for managing tasks was not Slack but a task tracker (I'd\nrecommend Trello). This is where you create an agreement about who is doing\nwhat and when. If you have an emergency you may call someone on his cellphone\n‚Ä¶ and if you can‚Äôt answer a cell phone call you are supposed to call back as\nsoon as possible."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"We also defined for the IT what classifies as an emergency. Basically only if\nour product was not usable by all our customers, for instance if the server is\ndown."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"There was also a special email address you could use to report bugs that\ndirectly affect individual customers. We guaranteed that emails sent there\nwould be dealt with within two hours during regular business hours."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ul","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"But protip #3 is the most important one:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3